  "body": "can someone fix the CI config and get the build flag passing? I'm surprised to see this unresolved and every PR showing failed tests for so long\r\n\r\nI'm happy to take a pass on it as well, some feedback on https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/.travis.yml\r\n\r\n1. can we remove the cocoapods / azure builds from travis? https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/.travis.yml#L174-L201 -- why are these here?\r\n2. can we remove the android builds? https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/.travis.yml#L136-L172\r\n\r\nmy thought is its better to have the tests passing for common targets like linux/osx systems and have travis working, and move the ios/android/other travis stuff to another branch/PR to merge once that is ready to be maintained properly, as well, when its actually relevant. I can't imagine anyone running geth on ios/android (unless its the ethrpc stuff) as the system requirements to run an actual node are extreme at the moment\r\n",
