    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "CI for PPA broke because Travis added NAT traversals and broke FTP. It was fixed in the v1.8.23 release.\r\n\r\nCI for Android is broken because Travis screwed around with some other firewall stuff, but we haven't yet found what or how to work around it. Keeping it red motivates us to find it eventually instead of ignoring it.\r\n\r\nCI for Android broke because upstream Go syscall package pushed a commit that made it unbuildable on non-linux arm64. We signaled it last week and it was fixed. CI is green on CocoaPods again.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nWhilst it's unfeasible to run a full ethereum node on mobile, it should be feasible to run a light client. We need that. Also shipping mobile libraries permits interacting with contracts even through infura or other remote servers, so they are still beneficial.",
